So even before it happens, he was celebrating this with his disciples.

35:15.772 --> 35:18.575
And something that we are commanded to continue to celebrate.

35:19.116 --> 35:23.000
And the Bible says, before we do this, as believers, we should pause and examine ourselves.

35:23.401 --> 35:26.824
So I want you all to bow your heads, and I'm gonna pray a prayer of forgiveness over all of us.

35:27.405 --> 35:35.634
If you've messed up in any way during this last week, or how long it's been since you've been here, man, make it right, just talk to God, confess your sins to him.

35:35.778 --> 35:36.319
Let me pray.

35:36.879 --> 35:44.048
Heavenly Father, before we partake of the bread in the cup this morning and in obedience to the scriptures, we pause to examine ourselves.

35:44.929 --> 35:52.678
If we have sinned against you in any way, thought, word, or deed, something we've done, maybe something we didn't do that we should have done.

35:52.718 --> 36:02.770
If we've not loved you with our whole heart, if we haven't loved our neighbors as ourselves, we pray for the sake of your beloved son, Jesus, who gave himself as a sacrifice for our sins.

36:03.170 --> 36:06.154
that you would have mercy on us and forgive us of all of our sins.

36:06.975 --> 36:12.822
And as people are reflecting right now, maybe you're visiting this morning, watching online, thinking, man, I've never experienced any of this stuff.

36:13.303 --> 36:14.584
Well, you can experience it right now.

36:14.724 --> 36:19.971
Just in your own words, ask Jesus to come into your life and to forgive you of your sins.

36:20.011 --> 36:26.179
And by the power of the Holy Spirit, God can start that miracle transformation in your hearts right now.

36:28.462 --> 36:28.722
Amen.

